%N A398064 Decimal expansion of Hadamard's Gamma function at x = 1/4.
%C A398064 The Hadamard function is an entire extension of the factorial function not equal to the gamma function. In other words, H(n) = (n-1)! for positive integers n.
%C A398064 Hadamard's function at x = 1/2 is A019704, whereas the function evaluated at x=-1 is A244009.
%D A398064 J. Hadamard, Sur L'Expression Du Produit 1·2·3· · · · ·(n-1) Par Une Fonction Entière (in French), Œuvres de Jacques Hadamard, Centre National de la Recherche Scientifiques, Paris, 1894.
%D A398064 H. M. Srivastava and Choi Junesang, Zeta and Q-Zeta Functions and Associated Series and Integrals, Elsevier Insights, 2012, p. 124. ISBN 978-0-12-385218-2.
%H A398064 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hadamard%27s_gamma_function">Hadamard's gamma function</a>.
%F A398064 Equals (psi(7/8)-psi(3/8))/(2*Gamma(3/4)) = (Pi+log(3-2*sqrt(2)))/(sqrt(2)*Gamma(3/4)) where psi(x) is the digamma function Gamma'(x)/Gamma(x).
%F A398064 Equals phi(-1, 1, -1/4)/Gamma(1/4) where phi is the Lerch transcendent.
%F A398064 Equals Gamma(1/4)*(1 + Sqrt(2)/(4*Pi)*(psi(1/8) - psi(5/8))).
%F A398064 Conjecture: H(x) = lim_{n->oo} n^{x+1} * Sum_{k=0..n} (-1)^k/(n+k) * binomial(x, k) such that H(1/4) = 0.79564036... . Changing the upper bound of the sum to oo yields Euler's product representation of the Gamma function.
%e A398064 0.795640362039563572666788194422654699343277002848572...
%p A398064 (Psi(7/8) - Psi(3/8))/(2*GAMMA(3/4));
%t A398064 RealDigits[(PolyGamma[0, 7/8] - PolyGamma[0, 3/8])/(2 Gamma[3/4]), 10, 105][[1]]
%Y A398064 Cf. A360375, A381340.
%K A398064 nonn,cons,new
%O A398064 0,1
